<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-771-758  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 771 758.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  August 20 1990 v12 n34 p13(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Users look forward to easing update nightmare; OS/2 2.0 canupgrade apps from server. (applications)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Flynn, Laurie.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Microsoft Corp's OS/2 2.0 provides users the capability forupgrading OS/2 workstations on a network without leaving theserver.andP;  The function can also ensure that all users on a networkare using the same version of an application.andP;  The new featurecould be the answer to microcomputer managers' usual nightmare,that is, upgrading an operating system throughout a largemicrocomputer network.andP;  Microsoft officials say it will be easyfor developers to modify software to take advantage of the upgradefunction.andP;  The function will be available through a hook in OS/22.0.andP;  The product is scheduled for release in 1991.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microsoft Corp. (product development).andO;Product:   OS/2 2.0 (Operating system) (product development).andO;Topic:     Product DevelopmentUpgradingSoftware ModificationClient/Server Architecture.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>